description: From wood +‎ -en. Dates from 1530s, gradually replaced treen (“made from a tree”), from Middle English treen, from Old English triewen.

adjectives.description: wooden (comparative more wooden, superlative most wooden)

examples:
On a recent windy day, hundreds of visitors climbed wooden stairs to take pictures in front of the glacier.
Audio (US)(file)

entries.meaning: (figuratively) As if made of wood; moving awkwardly, or speaking with dull lack of emotion.
